<li>The court must not punish anybody who was forced to do a crime — <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.mechon-mamre.org/p/pt/pt0522.htm#26">Deut. 22:26</a></li>
<li>A judge must not pity the murderer or assaulter at the trial — <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.mechon-mamre.org/p/pt/pt0519.htm#13">Deut. 19:13</a></li>
<li>A judge must not have mercy on the poor man at the trial — <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.mechon-mamre.org/p/pt/pt0319.htm#15">Lev. 19:15</a></li>
<li>A judge must not respect the great man at the trial — <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.mechon-mamre.org/p/pt/pt0319.htm#15">Lev. 19:15</a></li>
<li>A judge must not decide unjustly the case of the habitual transgressor — <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.mechon-mamre.org/p/pt/pt0223.htm#6">Ex. 23:6</a></li>
